From 86b983f51942275a40a6927de9c1924dde1200e9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 07:55:43 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 12/16] rocket: RK3576 full NPU soft-reset (CBUF reset,
 iommu-safe) + probes

Add the two CBUF resets (SRST_A/H_RKNN_CBUF) to the NPU node and run the
vendor's full NPU soft-reset once per power-up in runtime_resume, before
any IOMMU domain is attached, so the reset's disturbance of the MMU banks
lands on an unattached MMU and the first job re-attaches on a clean MMU
(reset-before-attach is iommu-safe; the old per-job mid-op CBUF reset was
not). Without the CBUF reset the CNA streams the full feature+weights from
DRAM but the CMAC reads zero from an uninitialised CBUF. Also carries the
session's conv0 instrumentation (CNA group / weight-buffer / counter probes).
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi |   5 +-
 drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_core.c       |  77 ++-
 drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_core.h       |  42 +-
 drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_drv.c        |  39 ++
 drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_drv.h        |   3 +
 drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_gem.c        |  43 +-
 drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c        | 688 ++++++++++++++++++++---
 7 files changed, 821 insertions(+), 76 deletions(-)

